  "bio": [
    "Giovanni Arvedi is the founder and owner of the Arvedi Group, a steelmaker based in the northern Italian city of Cremona.",
    "Arvedi comes from a long line of metal workers: his ancestors owned a small copper mine in northern Italy in the 17th century.",
    "He started two trading and manufacturing firms in 1963 and later opened a steel works in Cremona in 1970.",
    "In January 2022, the Arvedi Group acquired an 85% stake in Italian steel mill AST from ThyssenKrupp for a reported price of roughly $700 million.",
    "The AST acquisition brought the company's revenues to nearly $8 billion in 2022, making it one of Europe's largest steelmakers."
  ],
  "about": [
    "Arvedi also owns his hometown soccer team, Cremonese, which plays in Italy's top division Serie A as of the 2022-23 season.",
    "In 1984, Arvedi was awarded the title of Cavaliere del Lavoro, one of Italy's highest civilian honors."
  ]
